				<td colspan="2"><span>My advice, if you just can't take anymore Eldrig camping...
<br />
Don't worry too much about camping him.
<br />
I just recently got my guts from him while waiting on a rez after a ldon- I had made trips to camp him once or twice before, but both times my partner or I had to leave before we could even really locate the PH. It's been part of my agenda for about a month to just swing by Skyfire and though through Burning Woods spamming track incase I got lucky whenever I was waiting on a rez or a raid or LFG or whatever. 
<br />

<br />
On my old (retired, heh) main I took pickup groups to Chardok for a little over two straight weeks trying to get a drop. Half the time we didn't even get to the god forsaken camp, the respawns kept eatting us up while I attempted to break the camp and keep the captain room quelled at the same time.
<br />
At least I made some friends out of that <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> Eldrig just drives you and your partner, if you have one, insane.
<br />

<br />
If you're absolutley determined to finish this corner of the epic, though, I'm not going to deter you. I know that feeling well. (And yes, when I found him and at other points when I have seen him up before I picked up the bard, he was always near the wizard port in.)</span></td>
